    <a id="care"><h3>How to Care for your VL Jewelry</h3></a>
    <p>
      <span>
        Vanessa Lianne jewelry is all handmade and will change over time. Oxidized silver gradually fades with wear but can be re-oxidized. If you would like your item re-oxidized you may do this free of charge. Email <a href="mailto:info@vanessalianne.com" target="_top">info@vanessalianne.com</a> for more details.<br/><br/>
        While many people appreciate the unique patina of matte finished jewelry, it eventually shines with wear but can be re-matted using the light touch of a green 3M pad.
        Over time, silver and brass will oxidize. To clean your VL jewelry without removing the satin finish, use a paste of baking soda and water and rub it over the item in a circular motion with an old toothbrush.  You can use brass cleaner on your brass jewelry; follow the instructions on te bottle.  To avoid oxidation keep jewelry in a sealed container. 
